      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable to worry about serious conditions when experiencing intense symptoms, but migraines can indeed mimic those symptoms. However, it's always best to err on the side of caution. Taking extra strength ibuprofen and naproxen in combination could increase the risk of side effects like stomach upset, ulcers, or kidney issues, especially if taken frequently or in large amounts. I recommend taking one of the medications, starting with the lowest effective dose, and only if the symptoms are unbearable. If the pain is severe and persistent, or if you notice any new or concerning symptoms, you should seek medical attention as soon as possible.",
      "source": "target",
